FBIS4-62034 "drsov092_a_94023" FBIS-SOV-94-092 Daily Report 11 May 1994 RUSSIA INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS Yeltsin Calls For Joint Efforts in Bosnia Yeltsin Calls For Joint Efforts in Bosnia LD1105203894 Moscow ITAR-TASS in English 1940 GMT 11 May 94 LD1105203894 Moscow ITAR-TASS English BFN [Text] Bonn May 11 TASS -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin said the leaders of the United Nations, the European Union, the United States, Germany, Russia, Britain, France and Yugoslav republics must join their efforts in search of ways to resolve the Bosnian crisis. Speaking at a joint new conference after his talks with German Chancellor Helmut Kohl in Bonn on Wednesday, Yeltsin said that for holding a meeting at such a level all parties must be absolutely sure that they will solve the problem. It will also require comprehensive preparatory work, he added. The president said the foreign ministers have already held talks and begun working on the problem.
